title: Nazareth, Parkland boys soccer teams play to soggy draw (PHOTOS)
text:
Complete Box Score » 
The Nazareth and Parkland boys soccer teams played to a 1-1 draw in slippery conditions on Tuesday evening at Andrew S. Leh Stadium. 
Nazareth’s Ibraham Tounkara knotted the Eastern Pennsylvania Conference Skyline Division game with 16 minutes left in regulation. 
Tyler Madeira headed in a Ben Jago cross to put Parkland up 1-0 in the first half. 
Brandon Long made six saves for Nazareth and Jacob Varrato had 4 stops for the Trojans. 
Scroll through the gallery atop this post to see photos from the game.
